Subject: [PATCH] Restore legacy pre/post-care pages at their original URLs
 instead of redirecting

The previous commit (d43699f) wrongly treated several genuine pre/post-care
guides as dead legacy URLs and 301-redirected them away. They're still live
on the old Squarespace site (chinchilla-bear-5wrf.squarespace.com) and the
user wants them preserved at their original URLs rather than redirected.

Restored as real pages at their original flat URLs:
- /pre-post-hair-prp, /pre-post-chemical-peel, /pre-post-mnrf,
  /pre-post-laser-hair-removal, /pre-post-hydra-facial -- content matches
  the equivalent /care/*-care page 1:1 (same current clinical guidance),
  with rel=canonical pointing to that /care/ page to avoid duplicate-content
  issues while still serving real content at the old URL.
- /pre-and-postcare-carbon-facial -- genuinely new page, no /care/ equivalent
  existed; written from the Squarespace source, self-canonical, added to
  sitemap.xml.
- /laser-hair-removal-protocol -- also wrongly redirected in the last commit;
  turns out to be a unique clinical protocol/safety page (not a duplicate of
  the service page), restored with its original content, self-canonical,
  added to sitemap.xml.

Also fixed /body-contouring's redirect target: it was pointed at
/services/jordi-shape, but checking the Squarespace source showed it's
actually about HIFEM body toning, not Jordi Shape -- retargeted to
/services/hifem-body-toning.

Confirmed via direct fetch that /pre-post-care-1/laser-hair-removal--pre-&-
post-care, /pre-post-care-1/lash-extensions--pre-&-post-care and
/pre-post-mesotherapy-hair-treatment are genuinely gone even on the source
Squarespace site (true 404s / no distinct content) -- left those as
redirects to the closest current equivalent.
