+        <h1>Diode Laser Hair Removal: What to Expect, Care &amp; Safety</h1>
+        <p style="font-size:1.05rem; color:var(--color-text-light, #574C3F);">A closer look at how diode laser hair removal actually works, what a session feels like, and the safety protocols OPAL Radiant follows for every skin type.</p>
+        <p><a href="/services/laser-hair-removal-mumbai" class="btn btn--outline">See Laser Hair Removal details &rsaquo;</a></p>
+      </div>
+    </section>
+
+    <section class="section" style="background:var(--color-bg-alt, #F6F3EC);">
+      <div class="container container--narrow">
+        <h2>How It Works</h2>
+        <p>Diode lasers target melanin — the pigment in hair follicles — with a concentrated beam of light that heats and disables the follicle's ability to grow hair, while sparing the surrounding skin. Because the laser only affects hair that's actively in its growth phase, and hair grows in overlapping cycles, a full course typically needs <strong>6–8 sessions spaced a few weeks apart</strong> to catch every follicle as it cycles through.</p>
+      </div>
+    </section>
+
+    <section class="section">
+      <div class="container container--narrow">
+        <h2>What a Session Feels Like</h2>
+        <p>Most clients describe the sensation as <strong>a small snap or pinch, similar to a rubber band snapping</strong> against the skin — brief and localised rather than continuously painful. Our diode systems include integrated cooling to keep sessions comfortable, and sensitivity varies by area and individual pain threshold.</p>
+      </div>
+    </section>
+
+    <section class="section" style="background:var(--color-bg-alt, #F6F3EC);">
+      <div class="container container--narrow">
+        <h2>Preparing for Your Session</h2>
+        <ul class="care-list">
+          <li><strong>2–4 weeks before:</strong> Avoid plucking, waxing, threading or epilating — these remove the hair root the laser needs to target. Shaving is fine and recommended right up to your appointment.</li>
+          <li><strong>In the weeks before:</strong> Limit sun exposure and tanning on the treatment area; sunburned or heavily tanned skin increases the risk of pigment changes and can't be safely treated.</li>
+          <li><strong>On the day:</strong> Arrive with clean skin, free of deodorant, lotion, perfume or makeup on the treatment area.</li>
+        </ul>
+      </div>
+    </section>
+
+    <section class="section">
+      <div class="container container--narrow">
+        <h2>Aftercare</h2>
+        <ul class="care-list">
+          <li><strong>Soothing:</strong> A cool compress or soothing gel can help if the skin feels warm after treatment.</li>
+          <li><strong>Sun protection:</strong> Avoid direct sun exposure on the treated area and use sunscreen, since skin is more sun-sensitive right after treatment.</li>
+          <li><strong>Between sessions:</strong> Do not wax, pluck or thread the treated area — shaving is fine and won't affect the next session.</li>
+          <li><strong>Shedding:</strong> Treated hairs shed naturally over the following <strong>1–3 weeks</strong> — this is expected and is a sign the treatment is working, not regrowth.</li>
+          <li><strong>Gentle care:</strong> Keep the area moisturised and avoid harsh scrubs or exfoliants until any sensitivity has settled, and avoid hot showers, saunas, steam and swimming for 24–48 hours after each session.</li>
+        </ul>
+      </div>
+    </section>
+
+    <section class="section" style="background:#fff; border-top:1px solid var(--color-border, #D4CBC0); border-bottom:1px solid var(--color-border, #D4CBC0);">
+      <div class="container container--narrow">
+        <h2>Safety Protocols</h2>
+        <p>Every session at OPAL Radiant is performed under dermatologist supervision, with protective eyewear for both client and provider, and cooling technology to protect the skin's surface. Laser settings are calibrated to individual skin type — this matters especially for Indian/Fitzpatrick skin types III–V, which carry a higher risk of pigment changes if settings aren't properly adjusted.</p>
+        <h3 style="margin-top:1.5rem;">When Laser Hair Removal Isn't Recommended</h3>
+        <ul class="care-list care-list--alert">
+          <li>During pregnancy</li>
+          <li>Over active skin infections or open wounds in the treatment area</li>
+          <li>For clients with a history of keloid scarring in the treatment area (evaluated case-by-case)</li>
+          <li>Directly over tattoos in the treatment area, due to the risk of the ink absorbing laser energy</li>
+        </ul>
+        <p style="margin-top:1rem; color:var(--color-text-light, #574C3F);">If any of these apply to you, mention it during your consultation — Dr. Punit's team will advise on the safest path forward.</p>
+      </div>
+    </section>
