+
+    <section class="section" style="background:var(--color-bg-alt, #F6F3EC);">
+      <div class="container container--narrow">
+        <h2>Before Your Session</h2>
+        <p>Before your Carbon Laser Facial:</p>
+        <ul class="care-list">
+          <li><strong>2 weeks before:</strong> Limit sun exposure and avoid tanning beds — sunburned or freshly tanned skin cannot be safely treated. Use SPF 30+ daily and reapply frequently.</li>
+          <li><strong>Several days before:</strong> Discontinue retinoids, AHAs and BHAs on the treatment area so skin isn't overly sensitised going in.</li>
+          <li><strong>Before your appointment:</strong> Let us know about any active skin infections, cold sores, or if you're pregnant or breastfeeding. Stay well hydrated in the days leading up to treatment.</li>
+          <li><strong>On the day:</strong> Arrive with a clean, makeup-free face so the laser can be applied evenly.</li>
+        </ul>
+      </div>
+    </section>
+
+    <section class="section">
+      <div class="container container--narrow">
+        <h2>After Your Session</h2>
+        <p>After your Carbon Laser Facial:</p>
+        <ul class="care-list">
+          <li><strong>First 24–48 hours:</strong> Avoid makeup so freshly treated skin can settle undisturbed.</li>
+          <li><strong>First 2 weeks:</strong> Avoid direct sun exposure and reapply broad-spectrum sunscreen (SPF 30+) throughout the day — new skin is especially sun-sensitive after this treatment.</li>
+          <li><strong>Daily care:</strong> Cleanse gently with mild, non-irritating products and apply a fragrance-free moisturiser. Avoid heat and steam (saunas, steam rooms, very hot showers) in the first few days.</li>
+          <li><strong>Hands off:</strong> Avoid touching or picking at the treated area, even if you notice mild flaking.</li>
+          <li><strong>Between sessions:</strong> A course of 4–6 sessions spaced 2–4 weeks apart gives the most consistent results for pore size, oiliness and pigmentation — results build gradually over several weeks.</li>
+        </ul>
+      </div>
+    </section>
+
+    <section class="section" style="background:#fff; border-top:1px solid var(--color-border, #D4CBC0); border-bottom:1px solid var(--color-border, #D4CBC0);">
