+        <h2>What to Expect &amp; When to Call Us</h2>
+        <p>Mild, temporary redness and swelling are a normal part of the healing process. Please contact your clinic on <a href="tel:+917703037070"><strong>+91 77030 37070</strong></a> if you experience:</p>
+        <ul class="care-list care-list--alert">
+          <li>Blistering, crusting, or skin that looks unusually dark or discoloured</li>
+          <li>Redness or swelling that is severe, spreading, or not settling after a few days</li>
+          <li>Signs of infection — pus, warmth, or fever</li>
+          <li>An allergic-type reaction — hives, intense itching, or a rash</li>
+        </ul>
+        <p style="margin-top:1rem; color:var(--color-text-light, #574C3F);">These are precautionary — serious problems are uncommon, but early contact is always the safer choice.</p>
+      </div>
