+        <h1>Chemical Peel — Pre &amp; Post-Care Guide</h1>
+        <p style="font-size:1.05rem; color:var(--color-text-light, #574C3F);">Chemical peels work in layers over the following days. Your aftercare directly affects how even the peel is, how long it takes to settle, and how much you get out of each session.</p>
+        <p><a href="/services/chemical-peel" class="btn btn--outline">See Chemical Peel details &rsaquo;</a></p>
+      </div>
+    </section>
+
+    <section class="section" style="background:var(--color-bg-alt, #F6F3EC);">
+      <div class="container container--narrow">
+        <h2>Before Your Session</h2>
+        <p>Before your peel:</p>
+        <ul class="care-list">
+              <li><strong>4 weeks before:</strong> No isotretinoin (Roaccutane). No other peels, laser or waxing on the treatment area.</li>
+              <li><strong>1 week before:</strong> Stop retinoids, exfoliating acids and prescription actives. Avoid sun exposure and tanning.</li>
+              <li><strong>48 hours before:</strong> No waxing, threading or hair-removal creams on the treatment area.</li>
+              <li><strong>On the day:</strong> Arrive with clean skin — no makeup or heavy moisturiser. Come with realistic expectations: most peels build up over a course, one alone is a good "refresh".</li>
+        </ul>
+      </div>
+    </section>
+
+    <section class="section">
+      <div class="container container--narrow">
+        <h2>After Your Session</h2>
+        <p>After your peel:</p>
+        <ul class="care-list">
+              <li><strong>First 24 hours:</strong> Skin may feel warm, tight and slightly sensitive. Cleanse only with lukewarm water and a very gentle, fragrance-free cleanser.</li>
+              <li><strong>First 48 hours:</strong> Do not exercise intensely, avoid sweating, saunas and steam. Sleep on your back if possible.</li>
+              <li><strong>Days 2–5:</strong> Visible flaking or peeling is expected — this is the whole point. Do not pick, pull or scrub. Let it come away on its own.</li>
+              <li><strong>First 1–2 weeks:</strong> Broad-spectrum SPF 30+ daily is essential. Skip actives, retinoids and physical scrubs during this window.</li>
+              <li><strong>While peeling:</strong> Moisturise with a bland, fragrance-free moisturiser several times a day. No makeup for 24 hours minimum; longer for deeper peels.</li>
+              <li><strong>Between sessions:</strong> A course of 4–6 peels spaced 2–4 weeks apart gives cumulative results. Consistency matters more than any single session.</li>
+        </ul>
+      </div>
+    </section>
+
+    <section class="section" style="background:#fff; border-top:1px solid var(--color-border, #D4CBC0); border-bottom:1px solid var(--color-border, #D4CBC0);">
