+
+    <section class="section" style="background:var(--color-bg-alt, #F6F3EC);">
+      <div class="container container--narrow">
+        <h2>Before Your Session</h2>
+        <p>Before your PRP session:</p>
+        <ul class="care-list">
+              <li><strong>1 week before:</strong> Where medically safe, minimise blood-thinners (aspirin, ibuprofen, high-dose fish oil). Do not stop prescribed medication without asking your doctor. No alcohol for 48 hours.</li>
+              <li><strong>24 hours before:</strong> Drink plenty of water — hydration improves the quality of your PRP.</li>
+              <li><strong>The morning of:</strong> Eat a proper meal about 2 hours before your appointment. Have breakfast — never come fasting.</li>
+              <li><strong>On the day:</strong> Come with clean, freshly washed hair. No hair oil, styling products, serums or hair colour on the day of treatment.</li>
+        </ul>
+      </div>
+    </section>
+
+    <section class="section">
+      <div class="container container--narrow">
+        <h2>After Your Session</h2>
+        <p>After your PRP session:</p>
+        <ul class="care-list">
+              <li><strong>First 6 hours:</strong> Do not wash your hair. Do not touch or rub the scalp. Some tenderness, mild redness or pinpoint swelling at injection points is normal.</li>
+              <li><strong>First 24 hours:</strong> Skip vigorous exercise, saunas, steam rooms and swimming. No hair colour, chemical treatments or hair oil.</li>
+              <li><strong>Next day:</strong> You may wash your hair gently with a mild, sulphate-free shampoo. Pat dry — do not rub.</li>
+              <li><strong>First week:</strong> Avoid tight hairstyles that pull at the scalp. No head massage, hair oiling, chemical treatments or hair colour.</li>
+              <li><strong>First month:</strong> Sleep well, eat a protein-rich diet, and manage stress — PRP works better when your body is well nourished. Continue any topical treatments (like minoxidil) your dermatologist has prescribed, unless told otherwise.</li>
+              <li><strong>Course:</strong> A standard course is 4–6 sessions spaced 4 weeks apart. Results build gradually. Maintenance every 4–6 months keeps gains going.</li>
+        </ul>
+      </div>
+    </section>
+
+    <section class="section" style="background:#fff; border-top:1px solid var(--color-border, #D4CBC0); border-bottom:1px solid var(--color-border, #D4CBC0);">
+      <div class="container container--narrow">
+        <h2>When to Call Us</h2>
+        <p>Please contact your clinic on <a href="tel:+917703037070"><strong>+91 77030 37070</strong></a> if you experience any of the following after your Hair PRP session:</p>
+        <ul class="care-list care-list--alert">
