+        <h1>Hydra Facial — Pre &amp; Post-Care Guide</h1>
+        <p style="font-size:1.05rem; color:var(--color-text-light, #574C3F);">Hydra facial has effectively no downtime — that's part of what makes it a popular pre-event treatment. A little bit of prep and light aftercare helps you get more from every session.</p>
+        <p><a href="/services/hydra-facial" class="btn btn--outline">See Hydra Facial details &rsaquo;</a></p>
+      </div>
+    </section>
+
+    <section class="section" style="background:var(--color-bg-alt, #F6F3EC);">
+      <div class="container container--narrow">
+        <h2>Before Your Session</h2>
+        <p>Before your session:</p>
+        <ul class="care-list">
+              <li><strong>24–48 hours before:</strong> Skip retinoids, exfoliating acids and any strong active serums on the treatment area.</li>
+              <li><strong>24 hours before:</strong> No waxing, threading or bleaching on the treatment area. Avoid harsh scrubs and dermaplaning.</li>
+              <li><strong>On the day:</strong> Arrive with makeup off if possible — otherwise we'll cleanse it at the clinic. Come well-hydrated.</li>
+        </ul>
+      </div>
+    </section>
+
+    <section class="section">
+      <div class="container container--narrow">
+        <h2>After Your Session</h2>
+        <p>After your hydra facial:</p>
+        <ul class="care-list">
+              <li><strong>Immediately:</strong> Skin looks brighter, more hydrated and smoother — this is the immediate "glow" effect. There is essentially no downtime.</li>
+              <li><strong>First 6 hours:</strong> Skip heavy makeup and let the serums fully absorb. Water-based mineral makeup is fine after a couple of hours.</li>
+              <li><strong>First 24 hours:</strong> Skip saunas, steam rooms and hot yoga. No swimming — chlorine can irritate freshly exfoliated skin.</li>
+              <li><strong>First 48 hours:</strong> Skip retinoids, glycolic/salicylic acid and physical scrubs. Use gentle cleansing and moisturising only.</li>
+              <li><strong>Ongoing:</strong> Wear broad-spectrum SPF 30+ daily — hydra facial gently exfoliates, and protecting the fresh layer keeps the glow going. Monthly sessions give the best cumulative results.</li>
+        </ul>
+      </div>
+    </section>
+
+    <section class="section" style="background:#fff; border-top:1px solid var(--color-border, #D4CBC0); border-bottom:1px solid var(--color-border, #D4CBC0);">
+      <div class="container container--narrow">
+        <h2>When to Call Us</h2>
+        <p>Please contact your clinic on <a href="tel:+917703037070"><strong>+91 77030 37070</strong></a> if you experience any of the following after your Hydra Facial session:</p>
+        <ul class="care-list care-list--alert">
+              <li>Any unusual persistent redness, itching, or breakout beyond 48 hours</li>
+              <li>A reaction to a specific serum ingredient (rare, but tell us so we can adjust next time)</li>
+        </ul>
+        <p style="margin-top:1rem; color:var(--color-text-light, #574C3F);">These are precautionary — serious problems are uncommon, but early contact is always the safer choice.</p>
+      </div>
+    </section>
