+    <section class="section" style="background:var(--color-bg-alt, #F6F3EC);">
+      <div class="container container--narrow">
+        <h2>Before Your Session</h2>
+        <p>In the days leading up to your appointment:</p>
+        <ul class="care-list">
+              <li><strong>2–4 weeks before:</strong> Stop waxing, threading, plucking or bleaching the treatment area. Laser targets the hair root, and removing it beforehand leaves nothing for the laser to work on.</li>
+              <li><strong>2 weeks before:</strong> Avoid direct sun exposure, tanning beds and self-tanners. Tanned skin absorbs more laser energy and increases the risk of burns or pigment change.</li>
+              <li><strong>1 week before:</strong> Stop using retinoids, glycolic acid, salicylic acid or other exfoliating products on the treatment area.</li>
+              <li><strong>24 hours before:</strong> Shave the treatment area cleanly with a fresh razor. This is important — do not skip this step. Long hair on the surface reduces effectiveness and can cause discomfort.</li>
+              <li><strong>On the day:</strong> Come with clean skin — no makeup, deodorant, lotion, oil or perfume on the treatment area. Wear loose, comfortable clothing.</li>
+        </ul>
+      </div>
+    </section>
+
+    <section class="section">
+      <div class="container container--narrow">
+        <h2>After Your Session</h2>
+        <p>After your session:</p>
+        <ul class="care-list">
+              <li><strong>First 24 hours:</strong> Mild redness, warmth or slight swelling around the hair follicles is normal and usually settles within a few hours. Apply a cool compress if the area feels warm.</li>
+              <li><strong>First 48 hours:</strong> Avoid hot showers, saunas, steam rooms, swimming pools and intense exercise. Heat can irritate treated skin.</li>
+              <li><strong>First 2 weeks:</strong> Apply a broad-spectrum SPF 30+ sunscreen daily on any exposed treated area. Sun exposure is the biggest cause of complications after laser.</li>
+              <li><strong>First 2 weeks:</strong> Do not wax, thread, pluck or use hair-removal cream. You may shave between sessions if needed.</li>
+              <li><strong>1–3 weeks after:</strong> Treated hair will appear to grow, then shed on its own. This is normal — it is the follicle expelling dead hair, not new regrowth.</li>
+              <li><strong>Between sessions:</strong> Keep the area moisturised. Use gentle, fragrance-free cleansers on the treated area for a few days.</li>
+        </ul>
+      </div>
+    </section>
+
+    <section class="section" style="background:#fff; border-top:1px solid var(--color-border, #D4CBC0); border-bottom:1px solid var(--color-border, #D4CBC0);">
