+        <h1>MNRF (Microneedling with Radiofrequency) — Pre &amp; Post-Care Guide</h1>
+        <p style="font-size:1.05rem; color:var(--color-text-light, #574C3F);">MNRF triggers deep skin remodelling, and how you care for your skin before and after the session has a direct impact on how it heals and how much benefit you see.</p>
+        <p><a href="/services/mnrf" class="btn btn--outline">See MNRF (Microneedling with Radiofrequency) details &rsaquo;</a></p>
+      </div>
+    </section>
+
+    <section class="section" style="background:var(--color-bg-alt, #F6F3EC);">
+      <div class="container container--narrow">
+        <h2>Before Your Session</h2>
+        <p>Before your MNRF session:</p>
+        <ul class="care-list">
+              <li><strong>4 weeks before:</strong> No isotretinoin (Roaccutane). Please tell us if you have taken it in the last 6 months.</li>
+              <li><strong>2 weeks before:</strong> Avoid direct sun exposure, tanning beds and self-tanners. Do not have chemical peels or laser on the treatment area.</li>
+              <li><strong>5–7 days before:</strong> Stop retinoids, exfoliating acids (glycolic, salicylic, lactic) and any prescription actives on the treatment area.</li>
+              <li><strong>48 hours before:</strong> No waxing, threading or hair-removal creams on the treatment area.</li>
+              <li><strong>On the day:</strong> Arrive with clean skin — no makeup, sunscreen or moisturiser. Numbing cream will be applied at the clinic before treatment.</li>
+        </ul>
+      </div>
+    </section>
+
+    <section class="section">
+      <div class="container container--narrow">
+        <h2>After Your Session</h2>
+        <p>After your MNRF session:</p>
+        <ul class="care-list">
+              <li><strong>First 24 hours:</strong> Skin will feel warm, look red, and may feel slightly rough or "sandpapery" — this is normal. Pinpoint bleeding stops quickly. Avoid touching the area with unwashed hands.</li>
+              <li><strong>First 24 hours:</strong> Do not apply makeup, sunscreen, moisturiser or serums unless we've given you a specific post-care kit. Let the skin breathe.</li>
+              <li><strong>24–72 hours:</strong> Redness usually fades to a mild flush. Some clients see very fine, dry, sandy flaking — do not pick or peel it. Use only a gentle cleanser and a fragrance-free moisturiser.</li>
+              <li><strong>First 5 days:</strong> No active skincare (retinoids, acids, vitamin C). No makeup for at least 48 hours. No swimming pools, saunas, steam or intense exercise.</li>
+              <li><strong>First 2 weeks:</strong> Sun protection is essential — broad-spectrum SPF 30+ daily on any exposed area, reapplied through the day.</li>
+              <li><strong>2–8 weeks:</strong> Skin texture and firmness improves gradually. Continue gentle skincare. Reintroduce actives after 5–7 days once redness has fully settled.</li>
+        </ul>
+      </div>
+    </section>
+
